50|$|The August 1965 {{issue of}} National Geographic {{included}} a soundsheet of <b>the</b> <b>funeral</b> of Sir Winston Churchill narrated by David Brinkley. The recording has {{the sounds of}} <b>the</b> <b>funeral</b> procession to St. Paul's, a hymn sung by {{the leaders of the}} world, and an excerpt of <b>the</b> <b>funeral</b> sermon. Excerpts from various recordings of Churchill's speeches are included. The recording ends with bagpipes accompanying Churchill's coffin to <b>the</b> <b>funeral</b> barge on <b>the</b> Thames, as the public phase of <b>the</b> <b>funeral</b> ends.|$|R
